Boil a half-full kettle.

Meanwhile, trim the @green beans{150%g} and cut into thirds. Halve the @lime{1/2}.

Pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Boil the @jasmine rice{150%g}, ~{12-13%minutes}. Once cooked, drain, pop back in the pan and cover.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Drain the @king prawns{225%g}.

Once hot, fry the prawns and green beans, ~{4-5%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. 

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so it's no longer pink in the middle.

Add the @teriyaki sauce{75%g}, @sambal paste{15%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder) and @water{50%ml} to the pan.

Bring to the boil then simmer, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Squeeze in the lime juice, then remove from the heat.

Fluff up the rice and share between your #bowls{}.

Top with the prawns.

Sprinkle over the @roasted white sesame seeds{5%g}.

Enjoy!